title: show_file_contents()
brief: Display the contents of a file.
seealso: alert, msg, scroll_text_down, scroll_text_up, show_text, scroll_text_to
version: 0.25
----

<p>This function allows you to display the contents of a file to the user, which they may interact with.</p>
<p>The display of text requires the <a href="/lua/global_mode.html">global_mode</a> be set to <tt>text</tt>.</p>
<pre>
show_file_contents( "/etc/motd" )
<a href="/lua/global_mode.html">global_mode</a>( "text")
</pre>
